<subSubSection id="C36E58BDFF87C5619DC1F935C985D722" box="[199,1206,1772,1797]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCB0B36FF87C5619DC1F935C985D722" blockId="19.[151,1437,151,1904]" box="[199,1206,1772,1797]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis id="B900D724FF87C5619DC1F935CC6AD722" bold="true" box="[199,345,1772,1797]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Distribution</emphasis>
. Apparently restricted to the mallee of western Victoria and South 
<collectingCountry id="F3634BA6FF87C561994EF935C981D722" box="[1096,1202,1772,1797]" name="Australia" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36E58BDFF87C5619DC1F8D6CC66D757" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BCB0B36FF87C5619DC1F8D6CC66D757" blockId="19.[151,1437,151,1904]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis id="B900D724FF87C5619DC1F8D6CC2CD70F" bold="true" box="[199,287,1807,1832]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Biology</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7470B5FF87C5619C2AF8D6CCDAD70F" box="[300,489,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Byrrhidae" genus="Brachybyrrhulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="328" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B900D724FF87C5619C2AF8D6CCDAD70F" box="[300,489,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Brachybyrrhulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are among the most xerophilous of the Australian byrrhines, occurring in the mallee region of southwestern Victoria and South 
<collectingCountry id="F3634BA6FF87C5619FE4F8EDCE78D76A" box="[738,843,1844,1869]" name="Australia" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Australia</collectingCountry>
, an arid, sandy region dominated by several dwarf eucalypt species.
</paragraph>
